HPI 42 y/o F whom I was seeing previously as a psychiatrist at Bold Health for panic d/o. Reports since last visit sx are worsening- has had 2 panic attacks (one on way to taking parents to airport and another on way to pick up husband from airport where she had to turn around due to severity of sx). Now reports worsening fears of recurrent panic attacks, worsening daily anxiety. Therapy performed (45 min): Discussed triggers for panic attacks (when she will have to be relied upon, not wanting to be failure/disappointing others). Discussed patient's catastrophic thoughts during attack (that she will be incapacitated and negative effects this would cause to her children). Also discussed patient's attribution of feeling like a "failure", discussed more realistic interpretations. Discussed patient's need for "control", and counterintuitively that this actually worsens anxiety/panic sx. Current Psychiatric Medications sertraline 100mg daily alprazolam 0.25mg PRN

HPI 42 y/o F with panic attacks. Reports hasn't increased sertraline dose yet but will do so. Somewhat improved anxiety sx since lat visit despite "crazy hectic week at work". No full blown panic attacks since last visit. Therapy performed (45 min): Discussed patient's thought process during panic attack of not wanting to disappoint others. Discusses often feeling like a disappointment with her mom- her mom would gret angry with her without patient being able to predict what she did "wrong"- e.g. college weekend didn't introduce mom to friends/other parents. Would then feel remorse, wondering what she could have done differently. Often had sense of mom's reactions as "a landmine" if she couldn't figure out right steps to avoid her anger. Describes not feeling safe at home, "walking on eggshells". Describe in early 20's being "angry", but later "building empathy", although also now feeling a "block" with her mom of emotions. Describes her mom doesn't hug her but can't articulate how this makes her feel. Describes how she finds herself focusing on the positive to cope. Current Psychiatric Medications sertraline 100mg daily (will increase to 125mg) alprazolam 0.25mg PRN
